700688f-a.title: Bronx: Burke Avenue - Mickle Avenue
700688f-a.text:
Burke Ave., at M.ickle Ave. W.P.A. men are shown constructing a barrier near an embankment leading down to the tracks of the New York, Westchester and Boston Railroad. The houses in the background are on
Mickle Ave; on the east side of the tracks.
November 12, 1936.
Works Progress Administration.
Federal Art Project photo.
